{
  "text": "2.1. Laplacians and the heat equation. We consider weighted graphs and graph Laplacians as in [CITATION_1] with no killing term and with the additional assumption that our graphs are locally finite. That is, a graph G = (X, b, m) is a triple where X is a countable set of vertices, b : X \u00d7 X \u2192 [0, \u221e) is an edge weight which satisfies b(x, x) = 0, b(x, y) = b(y, x) and |{y | b(x, y) > 0}| < \u221e and m : X \u2192 (0, \u221e) is vertex measure which can be extended to all subsets of X by countable additivity.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "14581784"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "14581784": {
      "title": "Dirichlet forms and stochastic completeness of graphs and subgraphs",
      "abstract": "We study Laplacians on graphs and networks via regular Dirichlet forms. We give a sufficient geometric condition for essential selfadjointness and explicitly determine the generators of the associated semigroups on all $\\ell^p$, $1\\leq p < \\infty$, in this case. We characterize stochastic completeness thereby generalizing all earlier corresponding results for graph Laplacians. Finally, we study how stochastic completeness of a subgraph is related to stochastic completeness of the whole graph."
    }
  }
}